OL,3,CUK risks missing climate targets
OL,4,Cwithout rapid tree planting
OL,6,FHowever, analysis by the ECIU has
OL,7,Ffound that more than 70% of carbon
OL,8,Fremoval from new trees will come from
OL,9,Fthose planted within the next five
OL,10,Fyears, warning that the UK is
OL,11,Fcurrently behind on its tree planting
OL,12,Ftargets within this time frame.
OL,14,FThis is because trees need time to
OL,15,Fmature and establish themselves to be
OL,16,Feffective carbon removers. It means
OL,17,Fthose trees planted by 2030 will be
OL,18,Fthe most crucial in helping to achieve
OL,19,Fthe government's carbon removal goals.
